People may misunderstand the word "mokShayiShyAmi" (I s=
hall liberate) in that verse based on what their conditioning tells them li=
beration is. To get a correct understanding, one may need to combine knowle=
dge from other scriptures.
=C2=A0
As an example, if the body of one having =
an attachment to the body is afflicted with cancer, one may see it as a pro=
blem. Because one feels attachment and responsibility towards the body, one=
 may be thinking about how to fix it and may get agitated. So, one is not f=
ree from the negative repercussions of that cancer. But, when Ramana Mahars=
hi or Ramakrishna Paramahamsa had cancer, they did not view it as a problem=
 and displayed the same attitude and mental equanimity. So, while their *bo=
dies* experienced the repercussions of that cancer, "they" were free from t=
hem.
=C2=A0
If one has surrendered one's sense of duty/responsibility towar=
ds *everything* as Lord says in that verse ("sarva dharmAn parityajya"), wh=
ere "everything" inlcudes body, name, wife, children, properties etc, then =
anything bad (or good) happening to those entities will not touch one or bi=
nd one. One is "free" from those happenings. *That* liberation is what Lord=
 says he shall give and the pre-condition is to give up any sense of duty/r=
esponsibility towards anything.
