Though some =
people interpret "dharma" in this verse as a religious path, the real meani=
ng of dharma is "duty, that which is correct". We have a sense of responsib=
ility towards so many entities, stemming from our conditioning (vasana). Th=
is includes a sense of responsibility towards body, name, wife, children, p=
arents, relatives, community, country, religion, subjects of study (e.g. Jy=
otish) etc etc. Every sense of "I need to do this", whether noble or evil, =
comes from one's conditioning and *binds* one. If one surrenders all these,=
 i.e. effectively one surrenders one's entire conditioning, at Lord's feet =
and accepts whatever happens to one as god's prasad, then one is liberated.=

=C2=A0
Based on the "momentum" from actions before liberation, one may fac=
e various life situations even after liberation. In one case, one may get c=
ancer and die. In another case, one may roam the world and spread Sanatana =
Dharma. In another case, one may sit in a cave and meditate for 10,000 more=
 years. In another case, one may roam the streets looking like a mad person=
. In another case, one may continue to work as a day labourer. In another c=
ase, one may destroy a kingdom in a battle. And so on. In all these cases, =
the liberated being has surrendered all preferences, all likes and dislikes=
, all agendas, attachments and sense of resposibility towards everything on=
e has (body, name, wife, children etc and all attributes of the body-mind c=
omplex that once ruled the roost) and engages in spontaneous actions based =
on the circumstances one finds oneself in, based on pre-existing momentum. =
Nothing that happens to one binds one and nothing that one does binds one.
=
=C2=A0
Liberation does not mean that all of one's belongings (body, name, f=
amily, community etc) are "safe" and "well". Nor does it mean that one does=
 nothing. Things may keep happening to one and one may keep doing things. Y=
et, one is untouched by them, like a water drop on a lotus leaf, because on=
e has no desires, demands, preferences or agendas and accepts whatever Lord=
 gives.
